# How Do I Get Started Programming For The Arduboy?

Programming for the Arduboy is fun! It was designed to be easy, too. Currently, we are working on getting some step-by-step guides created for programming specifically with the Arduboy. You can always check the [Guides section](http://community.arduboy.com/c/arduboy/guides) to see what other people create.

To summarize, though, you'll need to:
 1. [Install the Arduino IDE](https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/Software), _which is the software you code your game with_
 2. Import the Arduboy Library, _which tells the software how to transform your code into an Arduboy game_
 3. Create a new sketch, _which is what we call the file that has all the code in it_
 4. Start writing your game
 5. Transfer that file to the Arduboy

Don't worry too much about specifics if you're new. Concepts in the C language that Arduboy uses are almost universal among programming languages, which means you can learn the basics on many different websites. For now, I'd suggest looking into [this introduction lesson](https://cvw.cac.cornell.edu/Cintro/default) by _Cornell Center for Advanced Computing_.

----------

# Did I Miss Anything?
 * There are some more great guides in the [Guides section of the forum](http://community.arduboy.com/c/arduboy/guides), so if there's anything more specific you are wondering about, be sure to check there!
 * If you have any questions, make a post in the [Help and Information section of the forum](http://community.arduboy.com/c/arduboy/help). We'll try to help you out as soon as we can.
 * Need help programming or just want to show off? We also have a [Development section to check out](http://community.arduboy.com/c/arduboy/development)!
 * Do you still have questions? Feel free to send me a private message and I'll try to help you out!
